{
 "name": "RPlog_Political_Repercussions",
 "title": "Political Repercussions",
 "summary": "In the ready room of the NRCV Audacity, the naval officer Rasi Cen reluctantly chairs a fraught meeting over a New Republic relief operation gone bloody. The furious Quarren leader Chaboub presents holos of mutilated dead and the pro-military Senator Lemos, a Mon Calamari, demands answers about the lethal force used. The unwashed, battle-worn Captain Vengan Draelis storms in straight from the combat zone and defiantly defends his Marines, even slamming his sidearm on the table and daring the Senator to charge him, while the stoic combat-medic Galatea and Colonel Kyrin look on. Tempers flare to the brink before Vengan offers a soldier's apology for a tissue-specimen order gone wrong; Lemos declines his offered commission, and a bristling truce settles as the Senator agrees to direct the Marines where they are most needed.",
